c) Shall be reviewed by the Defendant solely in the presence of Defense Counsel;
d) Shall not be possessed outside the presence of Defense Counsel, or maintained, by the Defendant;
e) Shall be made available for inspection by Defense Counsel and the Defendant, under the protection of law enforcement officers or employees; and
f) Shall not be copied or otherwise duplicated by Defense Counsel or the Defendant during such inspections.

15. The Defendant, Defense Counsel, Defense Staff, Defense Experts/Advisors, Potential Defense Witnesses, and Other Authorized Persons are prohibited from filing publicly as an attachment to a filing or excerpted within a filing any Confidential Information or Highly Confidential Information referenced in the Discovery, unless authorized by the Government in writing or by Order of the Court. Any such filings must be filed under seal, unless authorized by the Government in writing or by Order of the Court.
